This paper deals with the problem of sentiment classification of documents, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Naive Bayes, maximum entropy classification, and support vector machines, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
